I often partner with a friend's warrior.  With his dual wield he usually has the aggro.  I let him take it w/o healing him so as to not waste my hits.  However as soon as he gets below 2 bubs I hit a quick stun and taunt and we both continue fighting with me taking the damage.  <br>
<br>
By his careful use or nonuse of his taunt button and my stuns and taunts we find that we can turn the mob any way we want.  We can go much farther with both of us absorbing the damage as needed rather than me trying to continually heal him.<br>
<br>
I realize this isn't the way it works in a raid situation.  But this is a great tool for the everyday exp grinding. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=quixotimomniscience>Quixotim Omniscience</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/16/01 8:18:53 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.webcmg.com/quixsmallshot.jpg WIDTH=94 HIEGHT=281 BORDER=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Experiences at a bit lwr lvl</span><hr size=1> Bombuss that does work well with non-uber mobs.  Even xp group mobs in the high 50s work well with a paladin tanking.  One of the past posters noted, however, the other large difference between us and warriors.  Obviously defensive is the biggest, but our evaisve skills just blow: riposte, parry, and especially dodge.   <br>
<br>
